        <name>35.4.4.6 Defective items in a batch (NOT IN QUIZ)</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;h4 class="HELM_exercise"&gt; Exercise &lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt; From a batch of \({@its@}\) items of which \({@def@}\) are defective, exactly two items are chosen, one at a time, without replacement. Consider the events: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt; \(A = \{\text{the first item chosen is defective}\}\); &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; \(B = \{\text{both items chosen are defective}\}\); &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; \(C = \{\text{the second item chosen is defective}\}\); &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt; and calculate their corresponding probabilities, as fractions not decimals:
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt; \(\mathbb{P}(A)=\quad\)[[input:ans1]][[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]] &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; \(\mathbb{P}(B)=\quad\)[[input:ans2]][[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]] &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; \(\mathbb{P}(C)=\quad\)[[input:ans3]][[validation:ans3]][[feedback:prt3]] &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;h4 class="HELM_solution"&gt; Solution &lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Since an item is not replaced one it is chosen we have: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt; \(\mathbb{P}(A)={@ta1@}\) &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; \(\mathbb{P}(B)=\mathbb{P}(A\cap C)=\mathbb{P}(A)\mathbb{P}(C|A)= \frac{{@def@}}{{@its@}} \frac{{@defm1@}}{{@itsm1@}} = {@ta2@}\) &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; \(\mathbb{P}(C)=\mathbb{P}(A \cap C) + \mathbb{P}(A' \cap C) = \mathbb{P}(A)\mathbb{P}(C|A)+\mathbb{P}(A')\mathbb{P}(C|A') = {@ta2@} + \frac{{@notdef@}}{{@its@}} \frac{{@def@}}{{@itsm1@}}= {@ta3@}\)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</generalfeedback>
